CHANGES0004 - face-preserves-strict proved, skip rewritten

Rewrote skip function from with-based to recursive definition:
- Old: skip i j with fst j ≟ fst i (blocked definitional reduction)
- New: skip (0,_) (j,jp) = (suc j, jp)
       skip (suc _,_) (0,_) = (0, tt)
       skip {suc n} (suc i,ip) (suc j,jp) = fsuc (skip {n} (i,ip) (j,jp))
- Key property: skip (suc k, p) (fsuc j) = fsuc (skip (k, p') j) definitionally

Proved face-preserves-strict by three cases:
- (zero, p): snd ord (tail is already strictly ordered)
- (suc zero, p): is-trans for head gap + recursive call at (zero, tt)
- (suc (suc k), p): h< for head + recursive call at (suc k, p) on tail

